{
  "texts": [
    "Second, monetary policy is not detached from financial stability considerations.",
    "On the one hand, monetary policy is one of the key determinants of financial cycles (Miranda-Agrippino and Rey, 2020).",
    "On the other hand, regulation and macro-prudential policy are key determinants for stable financial markets, which are, in turn, a prerequisite for the conduct of a price stability-oriented monetary policy (BIS, 2016).",
    "This paper presents novel indices that identify monetary, fiscal and financial linkages in central bank communication.",
    "These policy-linkages can conceptually be differentiated into (i) monetary, fiscal and financial dominance and (ii) monetary-fiscal and monetary-financial coordination."
  ]
}